{
  "texts": [
    "All these approaches provide exact guarantees and a good utility of the resulting models, but they require significant resources.",
    "We have surveyed the state of the art in digital forgetting and machine unlearning in LLMs from several points of view.",
    "First, we have reviewed and characterized the motivation, the types, the requirements and the main approaches to digital forgetting in LLMs.",
    "Next, we have conducted the most comprehensive and up-to-date survey on unlearning methods for LLMs in the literature, encompassing 22 works, most of them published in 2023 and 2024.",
    "Unlearning methods have been organized according to a fine-grained taxonomy, which classifies them according to the type of modification they perform on the model and their fundamental working principle."
  ]
}